[{:pattern/id "f0/p0", :pattern/title "Core Infrastructure", :sigils [{:emoji "🙇", :hanzi "亏"} {:emoji "🔃", :hanzi "叉"}], :tokipona "lon", :hanzi "亏", :rationale "Core Infrastructure -> lon/亏: This is the foundation — without it, no layer interface can function"} {:pattern/id "f0/p1", :pattern/title "F0-F1 Interface (Memory Access)", :sigils [{:emoji "📁", :hanzi "忆"} {:emoji "👓", :hanzi "见"}], :tokipona "lipu", :hanzi "忆", :rationale "F0-F1 Interface (Memory Access) -> lipu/忆: If the human cannot easily access memory, F1 does not extend their capability"} {:pattern/id "f0/p2", :pattern/title "F0-F2 Interface (Agent Perception)", :sigils [{:emoji "📎", :hanzi "才"} {:emoji "👀", :hanzi "见"}], :tokipona "ilo", :hanzi "才", :rationale "F0-F2 Interface (Agent Perception) -> ilo/才: If the human cannot perceive agents, they cannot effectively collaborate with them"} {:pattern/id "f0/p3", :pattern/title "F0-F3 Interface (Verification Visibility)", :sigils [{:emoji "😄", :hanzi "正"} {:emoji "📁", :hanzi "正"}], :tokipona "pona", :hanzi "正", :rationale "F0-F3 Interface (Verification Visibility) -> pona/正: If the human cannot see verification status, they cannot trust or improve arguments"} {:pattern/id "f0/p4", :pattern/title "F0-F4 Interface (Hypertext Navigation)", :sigils [{:emoji "📁", :hanzi "文"} {:emoji "➰", :hanzi "久"}], :tokipona "lipu", :hanzi "文", :rationale "F0-F4 Interface (Hypertext Navigation) -> lipu/文: If the human cannot navigate hypertext fluidly, document relationships remain implicit"} {:pattern/id "f0/p5", :pattern/title "F0-F5 Interface (Pattern Work)", :sigils [{:emoji "💎", :hanzi "本"} {:emoji "🔃", :hanzi "去"}], :tokipona "kiwen", :hanzi "本", :rationale "F0-F5 Interface (Pattern Work) -> kiwen/本: If the human cannot perceive patterns, they cannot leverage compositional abstraction"} {:pattern/id "agency/bounded-lifecycle", :pattern/title "Every Resource Has a Bounded Lifecycle", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Every Resource Has a Bounded Lifecycle -> unknown/unknown: Unbounded state atoms are memory leaks. Race-prone cleanup creates intermittent failures that are impossible to reproduce. A database table without a retention policy eventually fills the disk; an atom without cleanup eventually fills the heap."} {:pattern/id "agency/delivery-receipt", :pattern/title "Every Message Gets a Receipt or an Explicit Failure", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Every Message Gets a Receipt or an Explicit Failure -> unknown/unknown: Without delivery receipts, the system confuses \"sent\" with \"delivered\" and \"no exception\" with \"success.\" This makes failures invisible and debugging impossible. A telephone system without ring/busy/unreachable signals is not a telephone system."} {:pattern/id "agency/identifier-separation", :pattern/title "Keep Transport Identifiers Separate From LLM Session Identifiers", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Keep Transport Identifiers Separate From LLM Session Identifiers -> unknown/unknown: Identity in a distributed system is a graph of references; if edges are mislabeled, the system becomes internally consistent but externally wrong. This is an Identifier Garden problem: without stewardship, identifiers drift and get repurposed, breaking provenance and continuity."} {:pattern/id "agency/invariants", :pattern/title "Agency Invariant Set", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Agency Invariant Set -> unknown/unknown: Agency is not different from a database just because it uses WebSockets instead of disk. A message that might arrive is not a message. A session-id that might be correct is not an identity. An error that might be logged is not an error. The invariants make these guarantees concrete and testable."} {:pattern/id "agency/loud-failure", :pattern/title "Errors Surface at the Layer That Caused Them", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Errors Surface at the Layer That Caused Them -> unknown/unknown: Silent errors make debugging impossible. When a standup fails and no agent responds, the operator has no trail: was the bell not sent? Was it sent but not received? Was it received but the agent crashed? Was the response generated but MUSN was down? Without layer-attributed errors, every failure investigation starts from zero."} {:pattern/id "agency/self-attribution", :pattern/title "Agents Speak for Themselves", :sigils [], :tokipona nil, :hanzi nil, :rationale "Agents Speak for Themselves -> unknown/unknown: Proxy posting breaks the audit trail. When output appears under agent X's identity but was posted by the server, you cannot distinguish between \"X said this\" and \"the server said X said this.\" In incident review, this ambiguity makes root cause analysis unreliable. A meeting transcript where one person takes notes for everyone is not the same as each person signing their own statement."}]